# RHEL provide flexibility to modify firewall by creating rules

1. direct rules : can be inserted hard coded value in tables , less flexible
  
2. rich rules : provide flexiblility to create custom rules , not available in firewall
   like rate limiting,port forwarding,masquerading

# rich rules options
--add-rich-rule='RULE'

--remove-rich-rule='RULE'

--query-rich-rule='RULE'

--list-rich-rules


